# Frontend Design Rules

## CSS Variables
Use these variables instead of hardcoded hex values to ensure consistency and theme support.

```css
:root {
  /* Brand Colors (Light Mode) */
  --color-primary:   #334155; /* Slate 700 - Main actions, active states */
  --color-secondary: #0D9488; /* Teal 600 - Accents, highlights (Darker Mint) */
  
  /* Feedback Colors (Subtle/Pastel) */
  --color-success:   #4ADE80; /* Pastel Green */
  --color-warning:   #FBBF24; /* Pastel Amber */
  --color-error:     #F87171; /* Pastel Red */
  --color-info:      #60A5FA; /* Pastel Blue */

  /* Light Theme Backgrounds */
  --bg-body:     #F8FAFC; /* Slate 50 */
  --bg-card:     #FFFFFF; /* White */
  --bg-terminal: #FFFFFF; /* White - All white look */

  /* Typography */
  --text-primary:   #0F172A; /* Slate 900 */
  --text-secondary: #475569; /* Slate 600 */
  --text-muted:     #94A3B8; /* Slate 400 */

  /* UI Elements */
  --border-color: #E2E8F0; /* Slate 200 */
}
```

## Implementation Guidelines

### 1. Color Usage
- **Primary (`--color-primary`)**: High-priority actions (buttons, tabs, active links). Adapted for light mode contrast.
- **Secondary (`--color-secondary`)**: Decorative accents, subtle highlights.
- **Text**:
  - Use `--text-primary` for headings and main content.
  - Use `--text-secondary` for descriptions and metadata.
  - Use `--text-muted` for placeholders and disabled states.

### 2. Code Style
- **Always use CSS variables** for colors.
- **Avoid inline styles**; use classes or styled components.
- **Mobile-First**: Write responsive styles using media queries for larger screens if needed, or stick to fluid layouts.

### 3. Typography
- **Font Stack**:
  - **Body/UI**: `IBM Plex Serif`, serif.
  - **Code/Terminal**: `IBM Plex Mono`, monospace.
- **Hierarchy**: distinct font weights and colors to establish clear visual hierarchy.

### 4. Spacing & Layout
- Use consistent padding/margins (multiples of 4px or 8px).
- **Cards**: Use `--bg-card` with `--border-color` for contained elements. Add hover effects for interactivity.

## Principles
- **Usability**: Clear navigation, accessible contrast, immediate feedback.
- **Readability**: High contrast, ample whitespace, clear typography.
- **Minimalism**: Every element must serve a purpose. Reduce visual noise.
